CNCP v1 24175
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11299: defineComponent function syntax makes component props strange",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:36.493234+00:00",
  "text": "defineComponent function syntax makes component props strange\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.4.31\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ncopy CompA and CompB code to local vite + vue + typescript project，you will see type error in Comp B like this：\r\n\r\n![图片](https://github.com/vuejs/core/assets/23648263/da78e405-76c2-4626-8345-a4888adf41ae)\r\n\r\n`text` props is not required，but the error says that it is necessary\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`text` props shoulden't necessary, there should be no error reported here\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nthere is a type error says that `text` props is necessary\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: Windows 11 10.0.22631\r\n    CPU: (16) x64 13th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-13500H\r\n    Memory: 3.26 GB / 15.68 GB\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 18.20.2 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.EXE\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.22 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\yarn.CMD\r\n    npm: 10.5.0 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\npm.CMD\r\n    pnpm: 9.4.0 - D:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\pnpm.CMD\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Edge: Chromium (126.0.2592.87)\r\n    Internet Explorer: 11.0.22621.3527\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nchange code to this will work\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport { h, defineComponent } from 'vue'\r\n\r\nexport default defineComponent<{ text?: string }>(\r\n  (props) => {\r\n    return () => h('span', props.text)\r\n  },\r\n  {\r\n    props: {\r\n      text: {\r\n        type: String\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n)\r\n\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
